-lrb- cnn -rrb- thousands of palestinians are trapped in the devastated yarmouk refugee camp in syria , which has mostly been seized by groups including isis , activists report .
the london-based syrian observatory for human rights says isis and the al qaeda-affiliated al-nusra front took control of 90 % of the camp in southern damascus .
calling the lives of yarmouk refugees `` profoundly threatened '' on sunday , the united nations relief and works agency issued a statement urging humanitarian aid access .
`` never has the hour been more desperate in the palestine refugee camp of yarmouk , '' the statement said .